node.text:
Thrilled to share that I’m partnering with @lactaid this year to share delicious, real dairy recipes for the whole family! First up – Overnight Oats inspired by our favorite @sesamestreet friend, Elmo. My family and I often find ourselves saying ‘no’ to dairy-filled dishes because they can cause stomach discomfort, but thanks to LACTAID, I can enjoy the creamy and delicious taste of dairy because LACTAID is 100% real milk, just without the lactose! This Elmo Overnight Oats recipe made with LACTAID Milk is a simple, healthy meal that I can make with my kids and is a favorite in my household. Check out the recipe below. #CookingWithComfort
 
Ingredients
• 3/4 cup old fashion oats
• 3/4 cup 1% Lactaid milk
• 1 tbsp honey
• 1 tsp chia seeds
• ½ tsp ground cinnamon
• ¼ tsp kosher salt
• 4-6 small strawberries, washed and hulled
• 1 tangerine
• 1 small apple
• Halved blueberries
 
Instructions
1. Whisk together the oats, and milk in a single size serving bowl. Stir in honey, chia seeds, cinnamon
and salt until fully combined.
2. Cover with plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight.
3. Remove bowl from refrigerator.
4. Thinly slice strawberries and arrange slightly overlapping over entire bowl, making sure to cover
the oat mixture.
5. To make Elmo’s nose, peel small tangerines and break into quarters keeping some segments still
together.
6. To make Elmo’s eyes, thinly slice small apples into rounds.
7. First place eyes on top of the strawberry to form Elmo’s eyes and place orange segments in place for
the nose.
8. Top the eyes (apple slices) with halved blueberry for the pupils.
9. Serve.

node.text: Seeing my brand @ShopAnser on the shelves @Target is truly a #levelup. I started Anser over a year ago because I kept asking myself “where’s the representation?” I didn't see women of color in the conversations about #selfcare care and I wanted to build a brand that was inclusive for everyone!

node.text: In celebration of @shopanser’s @Target launch, we put together this special Vision Board box with Anser bestsellers, a beautiful bedside tray, a hand mirror, water glass, and the box to re-use for YOUR vision board!! node.text: #ad I love nothing more than being a mom and I’m so lucky to love my job every day. As you know, it’s hard WORK being a mom – from meals, to work responsibilities, to precious family time and of course those never-ending laundry loads. But what if I told you there’s a smarter way to wash your clothes? Introducing @swashofficial laundry detergent from Whirlpool Corporation! It truly helps me take the guess work out of laundry (too much detergent? not enough? idk!). Its Precision Pour Cap actually pours the detergent FOR YOU, so you only pour what you need. No guessing and less messes. Click the link in my bio to get your own bottle exclusively on Amazon. #SwashAd #TheSmartWayToWash #Momlife

node.text:
You guys, I’m so excited to announce that if you preorder my cookbook The Quick Fix Kitchen now you will get access to an exclusive video tour of my pantry and a digital download of my tried and true meal prep guide!⁣
 ⁣
What to do:⁣
1. Pre-order a copy of The Quick Fix Kitchen from your favorite retailer⁣
2. Visit bit.ly/quickfixpreorder (link in bio) and enter your information into the form⁣
3. You’ll receive the bonuses when you hit ‘Submit’!⁣
 ⁣
This is some of my best quick fix advice for making life easier and more enjoyable, and you only get access to it if you preorder my book! #QuickFixKitchen⁣

Check out the flick of the toe tho. She’s a dancer.

node.text: The most important job I have ever had is being a mom to my two babies. #Pregnancy is such an incredible journey with so many ups and downs.  I’ve shared with you all my story - from my diagnosis with #endometriosis, to the birth of my son, @creehardrict and later my daughter, #Cairo.  I am honored to have the platform I do to emphasize the importance of #BumpDay.   We are here celebrating beautiful bumps and raising awareness about the urgent need for better maternal healthcare in the United States, especially for African American and Indigenous women, who face huge disparities in care.  Join me today, and everyday, in supporting this cause and post your #BumpDay photo.  Also I encourage you to go to https://www.whattoexpectproject.org/ and send an email to your elected officials urging them to take policy action that supports safe #pregnancies and healthy babies. ❤️

node.text:
In partnership with @lactaid, I am so excited to share this Cookie Skillet recipe, topped with
LACTAID Vanilla Ice Cream! Y’all know I LOVE ice cream, so of course I had to celebrate National
Ice Cream Day. This dessert is perfect for summer and especially for those who are sensitive to
lactose like me. LACTAID Ice Cream is creamy, delicious and made with 100% real milk and
cream, just without the lactose – so I can enjoy every last bite without experiencing stomach
discomfort. Check out the recipe below! #CookingWithComfort #NationalIceCreamDay
 
Ingredients
½ cup unsalted butter, melted
½ cup light brown sugar
¼ cup granulated sugar
½ tsp vanilla extract
1 large egg
1 ¼ cup all purpose flour
1 tsp baking powder
½ tsp kosher salt
1 cup dark chocolate chips
1 scoop Vanilla LACTAID Ice Cream per cookie
 
Instructions
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F.
Grease 9-inch cast iron pan or 2- 5inch cast iron pans with 1 tbsp butter. Set aside.
In large bowl, whisk butter, sugar, and vanilla extract until creamy.
Add 1 egg and whisk until light and creamy for about 1 minute.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt just until combined. Do not over mix.
Add in dark chocolate chips and stir just until incorporated.
Drop into pan and spread out evenly.
Bake for 20 – 25 minutes, rotating pan halfway through cooking, until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let cool for 10 minutes.
Top each slice with 1 scoop of ice cream.
